window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p><b>A world-shaking discovery. Elixirs coveted by gods. A frantic escape.</b></p> <p>Percy never wanted fame. A cast-off noble who dreams of nothing more than than <b>cleansing his cores</b>, he thought his alchemical breakthrough—Aurora Dew—would cover his needs and let him grow stronger. But when the <b>Divine Order</b> demands his secret on pain of death, Percy makes a single, fateful choice: he runs.</p> <p>Hiding in a forsaken town next to the Grisly Bog, Percy and the companions who joined him in self-imposed exile train in secret, <b>mastering arts unknown to this world</b>. Now that they're being hunted, their goals have shifted: <b>infiltrate the aristocracy</b>, take down House Tantalus—the <b>vampiric nobles</b> who murdered Percy’s parents—and seize the elixirs they need for ascension. But gods don’t forget, vampires don’t forgive, and <b>revenge-fueled cultivation</b> draws attention from predators in every corner of the cosmos.</p> <p><b>They want his secrets? They'll have to pry 'em from his cold, dead fingers.</b></p>"; 
